wait 0.5
wait 1.0
play "lephon_title.ogg" 1.0 loop 93728:170530
stop "lephon_menu.ogg" 4.0
wait 4.0

say "The name her first love gave her was \"L\"—simple and honest, but it became affectionate. 
Still, it was only one letter of her true name."

show "lephon/lephon_1_cut3.jpg" 0.2:0 0.2:0 0.7:0.7 fade(9,linear) normal
move "lephon/lephon_1_cut3.jpg" -60:0 26 sineout

say "Her name is special. A name without meaning apart from what she grants it.
Now hallowed within Arcaea's heart, it is the name of a new being beyond all."

say "This is true:
\"Lephon\" is One God."

say "\"$e:Lacrymira$\" is Another."

wait 2.0

hide "lephon/lephon_1_cut3.jpg" fade(0,linear)

hidetextbox

wait 4.0

show "lephon/lephon_bg2.jpg" 0.5:0 0.5:0 1.6:1.6 fade(6,linear) normal
move "lephon/lephon_bg2.jpg" 0:-1700 41 sineout

play "ascension.ogg" 0 loop
volume "ascension.ogg" 2.4 4.0

say "She looked into His Spine, into His Heart, 
and she saw there the shade of His soul. 
...So, she commanded Him."

say "—Lephon,
is in many ways inscrutable.
He does not hear prayer for He cannot hear. He does not listen to His children."

say "But still: to command Him—that's no miracle.
That is only the end of a hundred thousand ways; divine.
And to call it \"fate\" would be trite, too."

hide "lephon/lephon_bg2.jpg" fade(1.5,linear)

say "It is undeniable: Lacrymira was deserving."

hidetextbox

wait 2.5

show "lephon/lephon_1.jpg" 0.5:0 0.5:0 1.5:1.5 fade(0.2,linear) normal
show "lephon/2_lephon_1.jpg" 0.5:0 0.5:0 1.8:1.8 fade(6,linear) normal

scale "lephon/lephon_1.jpg" 1.6:1.6 30 sineout
scale "lephon/2_lephon_1.jpg" 1.5:1.5 4 sinein
wait 0.5
move "lephon/lephon_1.jpg" 0:-100 30 sineout
move "lephon/2_lephon_1.jpg" 0:-100 30 sineout

say ""

hide "lephon/2_lephon_1.jpg" fade(3,linear)

say "Hollowed and dried nerves long quiet of synaptic pulse warmed now with recognition.
That stoney back stirred with old feeling. The Heart of God shook,
and, for a moment, the Air went still."

say "This reality changed then. All \"knew\", all innately recognized that girl.
Changing Lephon at its core, she became Rule itself."

say "The girl spoke to God and made Him hear. She made her voice reach depths 
that only her eyes could see.
Those eyes Lephon had blessed her with, and the hands and fingers He had given her too."

say "She spoke in a tongue she did not know, but felt; told dead Lephon her desire.
Give a number, give a name—give perfection in these symbols, 
and grant this holy one everything."

show "lephon/lephon_1_cut3.jpg" 1:0 1:0 0.8:0.8 fade(4.5,linear) normal
move "lephon/lephon_1_cut3.jpg" 0:-150 35 sineout

say "Not just any number and name: \"hers\". Nell's.
Nell was one person who did not deserve grace.
Lephon agreed. Lacrymira would instead become his Legacy."

say "She raised her arm toward His bones.
And there, she shaped the lingering will of God."

show "black.png" 0.5:0.5 0.5:0.5 2000:960 fade(0,linear) normal

volume "ascension.ogg" 0.0 4.0
hidetextbox

wait 2.0
hide "lephon/lephon_1.jpg" fade(0.3,linear)
hide "lephon/lephon_1_cut3.jpg" fade(0.3,linear)
show "lephon/designant_j.jpg" 1:0 1:0 1.8:1.8 fade(6,linear) normal
move "lephon/designant_j.jpg" 0:-210 16 sineout

say "A new color was born amidst the forest of giant's gold threads. 
It was Her, Lacrymira, and it shined cold throughout all of space, 
into His Ribs and Spine, and beyond to the Terra and the Air."

hide "lephon/designant_j.jpg" fade(0.3,linear)
hide "black.png" fade(0.3,linear)
wait 1.0
show "lephon/designant_j.jpg" 0:0.2 0:0.2 1.8:1.8 fade(6,linear) normal
move "lephon/designant_j.jpg" 0:-210 16 sineout

say "Power filled Her body. Her right arm found its way back to Her, 
and She began to re-shape Herself to seal any wounds."

hide "lephon/designant_j.jpg" fade(0.3,linear)
wait 1.0
show "lephon/designant_j.jpg" 0.5:0.6 0.5:0.6 1.5:1.5 fade(6,linear) normal
move "lephon/designant_j.jpg" 0:-180 16 sineout

say "Lephon had listened to Her, and now He spoke again.
She would arise here, behind Him—and after Him:
Lacrymira, or—The Ascendent - 8th Seeker:"

say "\"$e:Insight$\"."

wait 2.0

say "After the flow of time resumed, She set Her healed eyes on the 2nd.
Witnessing the risen Insight, Faith realized with pain that Lephon's will had been set.
She fought against it—she did, but it was with the same futility as to fight a wave."

hide "lephon/designant_j.jpg" fade(1.5,linear)
show "white.png" 0.5:0.5 0.5:0.5 2000:960 fade(0.1,linear) normal
wait 0.1
hide "white.png" fade(0.3,linear)
wait 0.2
play "fracture5_epilogue.ogg" 3.0
volume "lephon_title.ogg" 0.0 8.0
show "2white.png" 0.5:0.5 0.5:0.5 2000:960 fade(0.1,linear) normal
wait 0.1
hide "2white.png" fade(0.75,linear)

say "Lacrymira overwhelmed her, and pressed her down against new land She had made. 
She summoned a miniature star above Faith's back, and made it collapse there—
rending the Seeker's body to nothing in only a few moments."
play "fracture4_epilogue.ogg" 3.0

say "She dismissed the destroyed star and after: all was quiet again."

say "The story steadily draws to its conclusion."

play "sand_epilogue.ogg" 2.0

say "Lacrymira did not leave Her mentor dead, She brought her down 
to the land She had crafted and revived the young woman, bringing 
her soul back and healing the body's wounds. "

play "woosh.ogg" 1.0
play "wind.ogg" 0.0 loop
volume "wind.ogg" 1.0 8.0
show "lephon/lephon_2_cut2.jpg" 0:1 0:1 1.1:1.1 fade(6,linear) normal
move "lephon/lephon_2_cut2.jpg" -300:0 35 sineout

say "But, with the two of them all alone there behind Lephon, Lacrymira standing and Nell on her knees,
Nell knew at once what Lacrymira had done in her absence—and she went a new kind of cold.
In all that it means: Nell had failed her child."

show "lephon/lephon_2_cut3.jpg" 0:1 0:1 1.6:1.6 fade(3,linear) normal
move "lephon/lephon_2_cut3.jpg" -150:0 17.5 sineout

say "\"...\"
Lacrymira looked down upon her silently. She looked deeply into her—into the core of her being.
And She asked, \"...Nell, why won't you come with me?\""

show "black.png" 0.5:0.5 0.5:0.5 2000:960 fade(0,linear) normal

say "It hadn't been said. She could see in Her sister's heart that the two of them were not aligned.
Within, She could see that her teacher wanted to \"beg her not to go\". Because
She had floated that idea so many times before: to become a god, and leave the world behind."

hide "lephon/lephon_2_cut2.jpg" fade(0.3,linear)
hide "lephon/lephon_2_cut3.jpg" fade(0.3,linear)
show "lephon/lephon_2_cut4.jpg" 1:1 1:1 1.25:1.25 fade(3,linear) normal
move "lephon/lephon_2_cut4.jpg" 100:0 17.5 sineout

say "\"Nell... you're alive again so SPEAK to me,\" said God.
Nell looked up at Her and finally replied, \"'Why won't I come'...? Why do you want to go?\""

say "They both knew Her answer, and yet Lacrymira still gave it: \"I can't live for anyone but myself.\""

say "\"You shouldn't either, Nell. You don't need to.
You won't be thanked for it. You won't be praised.
You will die at the hands of an angel, and no one but I will remember you.\""

say "\"We don't have to die, L,\" her teacher answered. \"Stay, and we...\""

say "Lacrymira slowly shook Her head. \"I can see it,\" She said,
\"there isn't any saving us from that end. Every Shaper here will die.\""

say "And Nell hung her head and shook it in turn. \"No,\" she said. \"I won't allow that—\""

play "memoryShift.ogg" 1.0
wait 0.5
hide "black.png" fade(0.3,linear)
hide "lephon/lephon_2_cut4.jpg" fade(0,linear)

say "\"Shut UP!!\""

say "Lacrymira roared. Her voice struck throughout everything, and made Nell for a moment still.
When Nell looked back to Her, Her eyes stared back wrathful."

say "\"I told you a lie, Nell,\" she continued in a trembling voice—trembling with rage,
\"I can live for you. Do you need me to say it? Do you need me to enunciate?
To put it to paper? To say so obviously that I love you!?\""

show "lephon/lephon_2_cut5.jpg" 0.4:1 0.4:1 1.1:1.1 fade(4,linear) normal
move "lephon/lephon_2_cut5.jpg" -300:0 35 sineout

say "Hearing this, her mentor shook and broke in expression.
Her eyes brimmed with tears, she hiccupped then.
Tears fell from her face. She cried. She continued to cry."

say "And Lacrymira, She shouted over Her mentor's tears—"

say "\"Of course I love you! Why would I still be standing here if not for you? I won't leave you. I can't.
You're too charming not to love.\""

say "\"You're nearly everything to me...
I don't want you to die! I hate the idea of you dying, Nell!\""

say "\"And great, now you're crying. Crying... And now you won't answer me!
Forlorn Nell, always caring and caring...! I could hate you for it. I do. I hate that in you, completely.
You waste everything you are on people so much less than you!\""

show "lephon/lephon_2_1.jpg" 0.5:0.6 0.5:0.6 1:1 fade(3,linear) normal

say "She stopped speaking. Her body was trembling now. Her cold eyes fell on the girl beneath her.
Nell shook her head. She would not abandon anyone.
Anyone, but for L."

say "And Lacrymira told her, with a voice like ice: \"You're sad.\""

say "\"That's right,\" God repeated, \"you're '$e:Forlorn$', and 8 can't belong to you.\""

say "Nell stared up at her student, who was now staring into Lephon's back."

say "\"You deserve a mark of ruin,\" said Lacrymira.
\"You deserve a hex. You will be '$e:6$'. Bear that cursed symbol forever.\""

play "epilogue_accept.ogg" 1.0
show "2white.png" 0.5:0.5 0.5:0.5 2000:960 fade(0.1,linear) normal
wait 0.1
hide "2white.png" fade(0.75,linear)

say "Deep in Lephon's heart, something new was 
scrawled upon a black canvas, and it became the new truth. 
Now changed, the only words \"Forlorn\" could give her student were \"I'm sorry...\""

show "black.png" 0.5:0.5 0.5:0.5 2000:960 fade(1,linear) normal
stop "wind.ogg" 5.0

say "And Lacrymira answered, \"You are.
But, Nell... I love you for that, too.\""

